Name: HubSpot CRM Tickets
Description: Work with tickets in the HubSpot CRM
Share Context: HubSpot CRM Context from ./tool.gpt
Tools: Create Ticket, Get Ticket, Delete Ticket, Update Ticket, Search Tickets
Tools: ./associations.gpt, ./properties.gpt, ./owners.gpt
Params: prompt: detailed request to be executed against the HubSpot API


Fulfill the users request: ${PROMPT}

Use the tools available to you.

---
Name: Create Ticket
Description: Creates a new ticket in the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: properties: a json object with all the properties of the ticket

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/createTicket.py

---
Name: Get Ticket
Description: Retrieves a ticket by ID from the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: ticket_id: the ID of the ticket to retrieve

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/getTicket.py

---
Name: Delete Ticket
Description: Deletes a ticket by ID from the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: ticket_id: the ID of the ticket to delete

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/deleteTicket.py

---
Name: Update Ticket
Description: Updates an existing ticket in the HubSpot CRM by ID
Credential: ./credential
Params: ticket_id: the ID of the ticket to update
Params: properties: a json object with all the properties of the ticket

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/updateTicket.py

---
Name: Search Tickets
Description: Searches for tickets in the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: filters: a json object with one or more keys in the format `{"<PROPERTY_NAME>":"<VALUE_TO_SEARCH_FOR>"}`. Each key in the json must be a valid property name returned by the 'HubSpot CRM Get Properties' tool.

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/searchTickets.py
